    Steps:

    • Log into Liferay Portal as 'test@liferay.com' using the password 'test'; if not logged in as 'test@liferay.com', then log out first --> PASSED
    • Permissions#setUpOrgRoleLoginUserPG --> FAILED
      • Open browser to '/web/guest' --> PASSED
      • Click on 'ADMIN' that should have a value of 'Admin' --> PASSED
      • Click on 'ADMIN_CONTROL_PANEL' that should have a value of 'Control Panel' --> PASSED
      • Click on 'CONTROL_PANEL_NAVIGATION' --> PASSED
      • Click on 'ADD' that should have a value of 'Add' --> PASSED
      • Click on 'ADD_USER' that should have a value of 'User' --> PASSED
      • Type to 'DETAILS_SCREEN_NAME_FIELD' the value 'usersn' --> PASSED
      • Type to 'DETAILS_EMAIL_ADDRESS_FIELD' the value 'userea@liferay.com' --> PASSED
      • Type to 'DETAILS_FIRST_NAME_FIELD' the value 'userfn' --> PASSED
      • Type to 'DETAILS_LAST_NAME_FIELD' the value 'userln' --> PASSED
      • Click on 'SAVE' that should have a value of 'Save' --> PASSED
      • Assert that 'SUCCESS_MESSAGE' equals the value 'Your request completed successfully.' --> FAILED
    • Log into Liferay Portal as 'test@liferay.com' using the password 'test'; if not logged in as 'test@liferay.com', then log out first --> PASSED
    • User#tearDownCP --> PASSED
    • Role#tearDownCP --> PASSED
    • Organization#tearDownCP --> PASSED
    • Site#tearDownCP --> PASSED
    • BlogsEntry#tearDownCP --> PASSED
    • Delete all pages except the Welcome Page --> PASSED

    Cause:

    ERROR: Element is not present at "//div[contains(@class,'alert') and contains(@class,'alert-success')]"
